```python
    # First, let's find dataset exemplars to observe the neuron's general behavior on different images
    activation_list, image_list = tools.dataset_exemplars(system)
```

```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Let's create a specific experiment to see if the neuron is selective for the Coca-Cola brand
    # We will create an image with Coca-Cola branding and another with Pepsi branding to see if there is a difference in activation
    prompts = ["a bottle of Coca-Cola on a table", "a bottle of Pepsi on a table"]
    images = tools.text2image(prompts)
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, prompts)
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, prompts, descriptions)
```

```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # To test if the neuron is sensitive to red-colored soda branding, let's compare activations of 
    # images featuring red soda brands vs. other colored soda brands
    prompts_red = ["a can of Dr Pepper on a table", "a can of Big Red on a table"]
    prompts_other_colors = ["a can of Mountain Dew on a table", "a can of 7UP on a table"]
    
    # Combine the two sets of prompts and generate the images
    combined_prompts = prompts_red + prompts_other_colors
    images = tools.text2image(combined_prompts)
    
    # Get neuron activations for these images
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    
    # Describe the images and focus on the highlighted regions
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, combined_prompts)
    
    # Save the experiment results and the descriptions
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, combined_prompts, descriptions)
```

```python
def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Let's conduct a comparative test using Coca-Cola and Pepsi again, while also comparing 
    # activations to another soft drink brand with no red in its branding
    prompts_soda = ["a can of Coca-Cola on a table", "a can of Pepsi on a table", "a can of Sprite on a table"]
    # Additionally, let's test a non-beverage red object to see if there's any considerable activation
    prompts_other_red = ["a red apple on a table"]
    
    combined_prompts = prompts_soda + prompts_other_red
    images = tools.text2image(combined_prompts)
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, combined_prompts)
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, combined_prompts, descriptions)
```
